captions.text: - How much alcohol is in this
- It's refreshing just to look at it.

- What do they say in
South Africa, cheers?
- It's like drinking a soft gust of air.

- If you told me I was
drinking alcohol right now
- I would too, and I'd get fake drunk too.
- It's like stained glass of meat.

- When your fingers get
really shriveled from water,
this is what they feel like.
- I could eat all of this.
- It's like you set up to make some jerky,
but after a day you get impatient

and so you're just like,
oh it's good enough.

- So, they're only girl
anchovies in there.

- It smells like what
they would feed penguins.
- Uh, this bread was so good until now.
- It just feels and tastes like pate.
- A bunch of fish washed up on a beach,
and then rotted there for a couple days,

and then we just ate
the sand underneath it.

- Yeah, so we definitely
just ate some dolphins.

- Rusks, that sounds so
good, right, look at this,
who's just up to no good.
That's what I imagine a prettier version
of the witch who ate Hansel and Gretel.

- It sort of looks like
Diglett, like the Pokemon.
This is the evolved form of Diglett.

- Smells like those crackers
you get at the pediatrician

and they'd be like, "Here's
a delicious cracker."
- You gotta have a bite to eat this.
- I would like to break this up
and crumble it over some ice cream.

- I feel like I would eat
this under circumstance,
but if I had a choice,
I wouldn't be like, "Give me the Oumas."

- This looks like what
everything we ate becomes.
- It looks like a giant Slim Jim.

Or just like, I guess
it would just be a Jim.

- This is like sausage that
your grandpa forgot about.

- If you heat this up, you
put some ketchup on it,
and maybe some mustard and a bun.
- Right off the bat these remind me of

Flotsam and Jetsam, or
his little evil friends.

It smells like anything
that you fry in oil.
- These are even better than the rusks.
If I could eat the Dough Boy, I would.

- [Man in Glasses] I feel
like everything we ate

was something you eat when
you're exceptionally drunk.

- Every single South
African food is amazing.

- [Woman with Black
Hair] This is a miracle.
